    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-25T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-25T09:00:00-05:00" n="603"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00 Supreme Soviet/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-25T17:00:00+03:00"
                            >February 25, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received February 25—2:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>367. The eighth session of the Supreme Soviet of the Union of Soviet Socialist
                    Republics opened today and adopted as the agenda discussion of the 1941 budget
                    and the ratification of acts of the Praesidium since the last session.<note
                        n="29" xml:id="d603fn29">The 1940 budget had been adopted at the sixth
                        session of the Supreme Council, March 29–April 4, 1940. The seventh session
                        had been held August 1–7, 1940.</note> I attended the opening meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
